task.summary: Default task
context menu is displayed by right clicking on an image in a gallery
Variable renamed in galleryView from gallery to image as it is the image thats being displayed in the datagrid. selectedImage added to ImageController. It is not set yet and the type is incorrect
Variable renamed in galleryView from gallery to image as it is the image thats being displayed in the datagrid.

An image can be deleted from a gallery by right clicking on it. The page has to be manually refresed to see the change though. Primefaces update seems to update the page before the deletion from the database has been completed.

Viewing an image details from the context menu did not work. I believe this was caused by the mouseover event resetting the id to null which meant there was nothing to display. I have moved the functionality to 3 buttons below the image. Only delete has been implemented so far. The look also needs improved.
aligned buttons beneath images. Renamed variable to selectedImageId.
Right clicking on the image now works to populate the description field with data. At the moment, it only populates using the id. To be refctored to display the correct information.
After right clicking, the imageView is now populated. ImageView Information still needs to be displayed on the page.
The image title can now be displayed by right-clicking on the selected image.
By right clicking on an image, the photographer and the date uploaded are shown in a popup.
Revision Number has been added to Revision and is displayed in the popup.
Check out popup added, backend code still to be done. Delete popup has confirmation of image title.
SaveNewImage has been moved to the ImageController from the GalleryController
The growl message works again and uploading a file now uses the one set of methods.
Images are now displayed on the front end using the head revision ID.
A download API has been added for use with checkout functionality.
A gallery can be deleted.
A file is downloaded when the checkout button is clicked. I have not used the API for this. Creating the new revision has still to be done.
When a user clicks the checkout button, the image is downloaded and the current revision is updated to be checked out by the user.
System Outs removed in checkout image. Popup now closes after clicking checkout.
Button appears beneath Image indicating it is currently checked out and can be checked back in. Check in functionality still to be done.
An image can be checked out, then a new revision of the image can be checked back in.
When an image is deleted, it is now removed from the screen automatically.
When an image is checked back in, the check in button dissapears.
Refactored so checking out can use the same code in the image controller for updating the galleryView.
Updated ImageViewList when a new ImageView is updated, the image still does not appear on the screen as it is being called from the header form.
The image frame is now shown on the galleryView after an image has been uploaded. The image is not displayed though.
When an image is deleted, a Growl message is displayed.
A gallery can be updated with new thumbnail. A growl message is displayed showing if the update has been successful.
In the view image information popup. The Revision number is displayed in a drop down list. Ajax is used to then update the label where the filename will go. Currently, the revisionId is displayed.
A user is able to select a previous revision from the image information popup and download it to there computer.
The menubar has been tidied up to remove unwanted options.
The image metadata class has been removed
An image can have a description and it is displayed on the Image Information popup.
A user can navigate to gallery 1, then go back to home, then enter a new gallery and the correct information is shown. Previously, the list of images was not being reset.
GalleryMetadata removed
A revision can have a revision comment.
Add the new id of the persisted Image to the ImageView
When an image is uploaded, it is shown on the screen automatically when the upload is complete.
When an image is checked in, a revsion comment can be added. Unique constraint on Image(Title, Gallery_id) added.
When an image is checked in, it is displayed on the page. Unique constraint added to revision(revision_number, image_id)
A gallery description is now displayed on the select gallery screen. Unique constraint added to files(revision_id).
A gallery description can be edited.
An Image description can be edited.
Logout button added to menubar. Removed logout menuitem
The users fullname is displayed on the right hand side of the menubar.
Gallery thumbnails resized to match images. When creating an new gallery, the description is set.
Variable renamed.
Available Galleries removed form GalleryController
